   <titleInfo>
      <title>Declining Earnings Of Young Men: Their Relation To Poverty, Teen Pregnancy, And Family Formation</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This report focuses primarily on the earnings and marriage rates of young men and how those earning losses of young males is directly linked to the problem of adolescent pregnancy and the declines in black family formation. The report also explores how earning potential is directly related to basic skills achievement, education level, and poverty.</abstract>
